	<dd style="color:611101 ;font-family:cursive">It is defined in the head'tag section of the HTML page inside the style'tag</dd>
	<dt style="color:F54927 ;font-size:20px">External CSS</dt>
	<dd style="color:611101 ;font-family:cursive">It is defined in anther css page andd link with html page<dd>
	</dl>
	-->
	<h1 id="head2">Internal CSS</h1>
	<p id="p2">Internal CSS, also known as embedded CSS, is a method of styling HTML elements by placing CSS rules directly within the head section of an HTML document. This approach allows for the styling of a single HTML page, providing unique aesthetics to that specific page without affecting other pages on a website</P>

	<h1 id="head3">External CSS</h1>
	<p id="p3">External CSS involves placing CSS rules in a separate file with a .css extension and linking it to an HTML document. This method promotes code organization, reusability, and easier maintenance for web projects.</p>
	
	
